From: jaewun <jaewun@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: qcom: qcs8550-ayn-thor: retain bottom touch power in suspend

Thor's lower FT5452 touchscreen cannot safely take the edt-ft5x06 driver's
normal reset/regulator poweroff path during deep suspend. Use the board-local
retain-power property so the controller remains powered without marking the
touch IRQ as a system wake source.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs8550-ayn-thor.dts | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs8550-ayn-thor.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs8550-ayn-thor.dts
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs8550-ayn-thor.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/qcs8550-ayn-thor.dts
@@ -393,6 +393,8 @@ touchscreen@38 {
 
 		touchscreen-inverted-x;
 
+		edt,retain-power-in-suspend;
+
 		no-regmap-bulk-read;
 	};
 };
